Fajana took this position while delivering the keynote address on the theme: “Human Capital Building and Sustainable Development In Africa: Issues, Options and Opportunities In The 21st Century” at the Annual Conference of the Department of Industrial Relations and Public Administration, Faculty of Management Sciences, Lagos State University on Tuesday.  Represented by Dr. Olaoluwa Joseph of the University of Lagos, Prof. Fajana postulated that students, schools, employers, governments and professional bodies must play some roles in order to achieve sustainable development. According to the egghead, sustainable development has emerged as a planning tool at the global level; adding that the United Nations had crafted 17 SDGs as a veritable tool to equate development around the world. 